// =============================================================================
// net/tls13/session/mod.vr — Typed-state TLS 1.3 session facade (spec §4.3)
// =============================================================================
// Layer: 7 (Session)
// Spec: internal/specs/tls-quic.md §4.3 — typed state machines
// =============================================================================
//
// Re-exports for the pure-Verum TLS 1.3 typed session surface:
//
//   * `state`: phase phantom types Handshaking / Established / Closed
//   * `client`: TlsClient<S> + Progress
//   * `server`: TlsServer<S> + ServerProgress
//
// The design is documented in each submodule. The intent is that once a
// handshake completes, you reach `Established` via a type transition —
// `write()` / `recv()` do not exist on `Handshaking`, so attempting to
// send application data mid-handshake is rejected by the type checker.
//
// =============================================================================

module core.net.tls13.session;

public module state;
public module client;
public module server;

// Re-exports
public mount .state.{Handshaking, Established, Closed};
public mount .client.{TlsClient, Progress};
public mount .server.{TlsServer, ServerProgress};
